<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0BFCFDD7FE9FFDCD" bold="true" box="[189,303,535,561]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F43FFAE0BFCFD86FE0BFBD5" blockId="61.[189,1399,582,1066]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
The Peruvian 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F43FFAE0A24FD86FE28FD9C" box="[357,408,582,608]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0962FD87FD1EFD9C" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[547,686,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garleppi">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0962FD87FD1EFD9C" box="[547,686,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. garleppi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “Callanga, Piñipiñi Valley”, is the 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F43FFAE0F1DFD86FB3FFD9C" box="[1116,1167,582,608]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
locality for several species. 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F43FFAE0A60FDA9FE04FD7F" author="Gade" box="[289,436,617,643]" firstAuthor="Gade" journalOrPublisher="University of Wisconsin Press, Madison, WI" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59150" refString="Gade D. W. 1999. Nature and Culture in the Andes. University of Wisconsin Press, Madison, WI." title="Nature and Culture in the Andes" treatmentTaxon="unknown" type="book" year="1999">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F43FFAE0A60FDA9FE04FD7F" author="Gade" box="[289,436,617,643]" firstAuthor="Gade" journalOrPublisher="University of Wisconsin Press, Madison, WI" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59150" refString="Gade D. W. 1999. Nature and Culture in the Andes. University of Wisconsin Press, Madison, WI." title="Nature and Culture in the Andes" type="book" year="1999">Gade (1999)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
discussed the valley and gave an altitude of about 
<quantity id="4C8A39C66F43FFAE0F4CFDA9FBD6FD7F" box="[1037,1126,617,644]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
a.s.l., while discussing the confusion over the place name “Callanga”. According to Peruvian entomologist Julio Rivera (pers. comm.) the ʻcorrectʼ Callanga is in 
<collectingRegion id="49B65AC16F43FFAE0932FD6FFC9FFD35" box="[627,815,687,713]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Cusco Province</collectingRegion>
at coordinates 
<geoCoordinate id="EE46F2E46F43FFAE08ADFD6EFB12FD35" box="[1004,1186,686,714]" degrees="12" direction="south" minutes="50" orientation="latitude" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" precision="1" seconds="16.80" value="-12.837999">12°50ʹ16.80ʺ S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE46F2E46F43FFAE0FF3FD6EFAC3FD36" box="[1202,1395,686,714]" degrees="71" direction="west" minutes="48" orientation="longitude" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" precision="1" seconds="28.20" value="-71.80784">71°48ʹ28.20ʺ W</geoCoordinate>
. Several species are known only from older 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F43FFAE0985FD13FD47FD11" box="[708,759,723,749]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
material at that locality, so it would be very useful to have new specimens from the area. The collector is listed as Otto Garlepp, but 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F43FFAE0F1BFD36FAADFCEC" author="Papavero" box="[1114,1309,758,784]" firstAuthor="Papavero" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59361" refString="Papavero N. 1973. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2. Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo." title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2" treatmentTaxon="unknown" type="book" year="1973">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F43FFAE0F1BFD36FAADFCEC" author="Papavero" box="[1114,1309,758,784]" firstAuthor="Papavero" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59361" refString="Papavero N. 1973. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2. Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo." title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2" type="book" year="1973">Papavero (1973)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
did not mention the highlands of 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F43FFAE0AB4FCD9FD9BFCCF" box="[501,555,793,819]" name="Peru" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Peru</collectingCountry>
among the localities at which Otto Garlepp collected. Otto Garlepp’s brother, Gustav Garlepp, is known to have collected at the “High 
<collectingRegion id="49B65AC16F43FFAE0F45FCFCFB00FCAA" box="[1028,1200,828,854]" country="Peru" name="Ucayali" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Ucayali River</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F43FFAE0F83FCFCFB4EFCAA" box="[1218,1278,828,854]" name="Peru" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Peru</collectingCountry>
”. Piñipiñi specimens also appear in the 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F43FFAE096EFCA0FDD2FC86" box="[559,610,864,890]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE09A2FCA0FC65FC86" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[739,981,864,890]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infestus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE09A2FCA0FC65FC86" box="[739,981,864,890]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Mesoconius infestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F43FFAE08A8FCA0FAC1FC85" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1001,1393,863,889]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="obtusiconus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="M. obtusiconus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE08A8FCA0FAC1FC85" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1001,1393,863,889]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE08A8FCA0FB12FC85" box="[1001,1186,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. obtusiconus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F43FFAE0FEFFC9FFAC1FC85" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[1198,1393,863,889]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0BFCFC43FEEDFC61" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1992" box="[189,349,899,925]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0BFCFC43FEEDFC61" box="[189,349,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0ADAFC43FD86FC61" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[411,566,899,925]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufithorax">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0ADAFC43FD86FC61" box="[411,566,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. rufithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as in those of many species of other micropezid genera. Almost all of these are rare species, known only from one or a few low-quality specimens. In most cases, the Piñipiñi localities are cited as “ 
<quantity id="4C8A39C66F43FFAE0974FC09FD23FC1F" box="[565,659,969,996]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
high, 1900”, and most are attributed to O. Garlepp, although 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F43FFAE0BFCFC2CFE24FBFA" author="Papavero's" box="[189,404,1004,1030]" firstAuthor="Papavero's" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59361" refString="Papavero N. 1973. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2. Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo." title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2" treatmentTaxon="M. obtusiconus" type="book" year="1973">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F43FFAE0BFCFC2CFE24FBFA" author="Papavero's" box="[189,404,1004,1030]" firstAuthor="Papavero's" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref59361" refString="Papavero N. 1973. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2. Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo." title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2" type="book" year="1973">Papavero’s (1973)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
summary of the Garlepp brothers’ travels in South America does not place either of them in 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F43FFAE0A5CFBD0FEE3FBD6" box="[285,339,1040,1066]" name="Peru" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Peru</collectingCountry>
in 1900.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368C7A86F43FFAE0BFCFB89FE0CFB56" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F43FFAE0BFCFB89FE0CFB56" blockId="61.[189,1399,1097,1194]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F43FFAE0BFCFB89FDD0FB9F" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,608,1097,1123]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Tanypoda" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="garleppi" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="Tanypoda garleppi" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0BFCFB89FDD0FB9F" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,608,1097,1123]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Tanypoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garleppi">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0BFCFB89FE2AFB9F" box="[189,410,1097,1123]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Tanypoda garleppi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F43FFAE0AE3FB89FDD0FB9F" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[418,608,1097,1123]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, until recently treated as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0F63FB89FB73FB9F" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1058,1219,1097,1123]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Zelatractodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0F63FB89FB73FB9F" box="[1058,1219,1097,1123]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Zelatractodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is here treated as a secondary junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0921FBADFCE7FB7A" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[608,855,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garleppi">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0921FBADFCE7FB7A" box="[608,855,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Mesoconius garleppi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it is redescribed below as 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0FDDFBADFB49FB7A" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1180,1273,1133,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ottoi" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0FDDFBADFB49FB7A" box="[1180,1273,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. ottoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F43FFAE0E40FBADFAC7FB7B" box="[1281,1399,1133,1159]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F43FFAE0A47FB50FED8FB55" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[262,360,1168,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nono">
<emphasis id="B90648316F43FFAE0A47FB50FED8FB55" box="[262,360,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. nono</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
